# Rust / Soroban (build outputs only; circuit wasm under circuits/ is committed)
contracts/target/
contracts/**/target/
Cargo.lock

# ZK circuits — ignore large/regenerable setup artifacts and test outputs.
# The RUNTIME artifacts (witness wasm, final zkey, verification key) ARE
# committed so the deployed app and the on-chain verifier work without a rebuild.
circuits/**/*.r1cs
circuits/**/*.sym
circuits/**/*.wtns
circuits/**/*.ptau
circuits/**/*_0.zkey
circuits/**/input*.json
circuits/**/proof*.json
circuits/**/public*.json

# Generated receipts / PDFs
/tmp
*.pdf
!docs/**/*.pdf

# Coverage / tests
/coverage

# Local tool binaries (e.g. downloaded circom)
/tools

# Local working notes / scratch (not versioned)
/temp

# Internal docs kept out of the public repo (responsible disclosure / scratch).
# SECURITY.md (the public security policy) IS tracked; the audit log is not.
SECURITY_AUDIT.md
DECISOES_FUTURAS.md
IMPLEMENTATION_INVENTORY.md
circuits/payment_proof/ceremony_out/

# Local scratch, never committed
temp/

# Remotion pitch/demo video project lives in temp/, never committed
/video/

# Claude Code and design-pipeline tooling, never committed
.claude/
.design/projects/

# PWA service worker (generated by @serwist/next at build)
/public/sw.js
/public/sw.js.map
/public/swe-worker-*.js
